{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/26114.The_Joke", "title": "The Joke", "titleComplete": "The Joke", "description": "All too often, this brilliant novel of thwarted love and revenge miscarried has been read for its political implications. Now though, a quarter century after The Joke was first published, and several years after the collapse of the Soviet-imposed Czechoslovak regime, it becomes easier to put such implications into perspective in favor of valuing the book (and all Kundera 's work) as what it truly is: great, stirring literature, that sheds new light on the eternal themes of human existence.The present edition provides English-language readers an important further means toward revaluation of The Joke. For reasons he describes in his Author's Note, Milan Kundera devoted much time to creating (with the assistance of his American publisher-editor) a completely revised translation that reflects his original as closely as any translation possibly can: reflects it in its fidelity not only to the words and syntax but also to the characteristic dictions and tonalities of the novel's narrators. The result is nothing less than the restoration of a classic.", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1448044837i/26114.jpg", "genres": ["Novels", "Literature", "Classics", "Historical Fiction", "Literary Fiction", "20th Century", "Czech Literature", "Fiction", "Philosophy", "Contemporary"], "publisher": "Faber and Faber", "author": ["Milan Kundera"], "publishDate": 694252800000, "places": ["Slovakia"], "ratingHistogram": [272, 1313, 7242, 14984, 11624], "ratingsCount": 35435, "reviewsCount": 1901, "numPages": 371, "language": "English"}
{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/741618.Six_Characters_in_Search_of_an_Author", "title": "Six Characters in Search of an Author", "titleComplete": "Six Characters in Search of an Author", "description": "One of the major figures of modern theater, Luigi Pirandello (1867\u20131936) wrote dramas and satires that sparked controversy with their radical departures from conventional theatrical techniques. His most celebrated work, Six Characters in Search of an Author, embodies the Nobel Prize-winning playwright's innovations by presenting an open-ended drama on a stage without sets.First performed in 1923, this intellectual comedy introduces six individuals to a stage where a company of actors has assembled for a rehearsal. Claiming to be the incomplete, unused creations of an author's imagination, they demand lines for a story that will explain the details of their lives. In ensuing scenes, these \"real-life characters,\" all professing to be part of an extended family, produce a drama of sorts \u2014 punctuated by disagreements, interruptions, and arguments. In the end they are dismissed by the irate manager, their dilemma unsolved and the \"truth\" a matter of individual viewpoints.A tour de force exploring the many faces of reality, this classic is now available in an inexpensive edition that will be welcomed by amateur theatrical groups as well as by students of drama.", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1373814414i/741618.jpg", "genres": ["School", "Theatre", "Drama", "Italy", "Literature", "Nobel Prize", "Classics", "Italian Literature", "Plays", "Fiction"], "asin": "0486299929", "isbn": "0486299929", "isbn13": "9780486299921", "publisher": "Dover Publications", "author": ["Edward Storer", "Luigi Pirandello"], "publishDate": 868604400000, "characters": ["La madre", "Housekeeper", "Editor", "La figliastra", "Il giovinetto", "Exec", "Mother", "Dr Lully", "Boy", "Theatre Maker", "La bambina"