{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/2052.The_Big_Sleep", "title": "The Big Sleep", "titleComplete": "The Big Sleep (Philip Marlowe, #1)", "description": "Down these mean streets a man must go who is not himself mean, who is neither tarnished nor afraid....He is the hero; he is everything. He must be a complete man and a common man and yet an unusual man.This is the Code of the Private Eye as defined by Raymond Chandler in his 1944 essay The Simple Act of Murder. Such a man was Philip Marlowe, private eye, an educated, heroic, streetwise, rugged individualist and the hero of Chandler's first novel, The Big Sleep. This work established Chandler as the master of the 'hard-boiled' detective novel, and his articulate and literary style of writing won him a large audience, which ranged from the man in the street to the most sophisticated intellectual.", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1371584712i/2052.jpg", "genres": ["Crime", "American", "Detective", "Novels", "Noir", "Thriller", "Classics", "Mystery", "Mystery Thriller", "Fiction"], "asin": "0394758285", "isbn": "0394758285", "isbn13": "9780394758282", "publisher": "Vintage Crime", "series": ["Philip Marlowe"], "author": ["Raymond Chandler"], "publishDate": 584694000000, "characters": ["Joe Brody", "Bernie Ohls", "Agnes Lozelle", "Mona Mars", "Philip Marlowe", "Rusty Regan", "Eddie Mars", "Carmen Sternwood", "Vivian Regan", "General Guy Sternwood", "Owen Taylor", "Harry Jones", "Carol Lundgren", "Lash Camino", "Arthur Gwynn Geiger"], "places": ["California", "Hollywood, Los Angeles, California", "Los Angeles, California"], "ratingHistogram": [3736, 8609, 31625, 57615, 52961], "ratingsCount": 154546, "reviewsCount": 7803, "numPages": 231, "language": "English", "awards": [{"name": "Anthony Award", "awardedAt": 946713600000, "category": "Best Novel of the Century", "hasWon": null}, {"name": "CWA Best Ever", "awardedAt": 1357027200000, "category": 